<br>
The Mines:<br>
<br>
The mines themselves are not very large containing only 4 mobs on the upper level and 9 or 10 mobs on the lower level but trust me this will be more then enough..<br>
<br>
The best thing to do is run around this place invis for about 5 or 10 minutes and you will learn that its an amazingly simply configuration.  Once you learn mob spawn locs and in the case of the upper portion the mobs pathing locs. the rest is easy.. <br>
<br>
You can easily solo 2 to 3 per full rack of mana at level 34--2 kills btw will give you slightly less then a blue bubble of xps, as in it takes 11 kills or so per yellow bubble, 55 or so kills per level.  As you level up and get more mana the number of kills per rack of mana will go up to 4 or even 5 with a good pet.<br>
<br>
The only mob that is social of the (bat, goo, spider or rat) that spawn are the spiders.  If its any other mob combo pulling with a spell, arrow or throwing item will bring you only one mob- even if theyre sitting right on top of each other.  IF and when 2 spiders spawn simply whack them and drag them out of the mines, take a right and first building on your right lives the quad 300 hitting rogue guildmaster-he'll do away with the pesky spiders-allowing you to hope for a non-double spider pop.<br>
<br>
I would camp in the lower level, either on the near side-pulling the 2 mobs across the river or invis up and run all the way to the back of the lower level and hunt the 3 spawn (hunting the 3 spawn in the back virtually assures total privacy -few folks ever go back that far) and No training,hunting the near side of the lower level might get ya trained once or twice.  <br>
<br>
Bind at the entrance to Icewell keep..If you have a runnner and pick up additional mobs-dont wait-immediatly gate to icewell and either summon a new pet or zone and restart.<br>
<br>
KEEP THE HEADS FROM THE GOO'S..these heads give great faction for giants if and when you decide to destroy your dwarf faction and ally with the Giants these heads will raise your faction insanely fast  4 heads=about 50 dwarf killings..You need to be non kos to turn the heads into Giants and it WILL make you KOS with the dwarves very fast.  If you are keeping Dwarf faction (reccomended for this camp) then save the heads till later or sell them to the high level dwarf killers who are working on faction--I have sold heads for 50plat -250 plat each--once sold 12 heads x 250plat.  (one level down there should getya about 15 heads).<br>
<br>
Mobs drop from 5 cooper to 5 plat each. Coldain beards and the occasional gem..<br>
<br>
Trust me folks on this camp...Its amazing, its safe if you bind near icewell, its fun if you learn the mines and learn where the pulls are, it can be non stop-when you near level 39 youll be doing 4-5 per sleeve of mana.. and it can make you rather wealthy..best of all its some of the best solo exps i have EVER seen... <p><center>
