<br>
I'd normally park my pet somewhere in the tunnel to the right as you come up the ladder, or even all the way at the end of it, and pull to my pet. Once the pet engages you can head back out and get good line of sight for bolts.<br>
<br>
If things go well you should easily keep the 2 ladder spawns and the 3 back spawns (the non-Norman spawns) clear with 2-3 minutes between pops. This will allow you to squeeze in the occasional Norman spawn (when you can get to them first) or the occasional front spawn as mana allows. If you're duoing (not bad xp if you can get all the lower level spawns), just park a pet on the Norman spawns spawn point.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
When breaking things up, double spiders can be dealt with reliably by sending your pet in 1st, heal, blaze, heal, blaze, blaze the 1st spider (/assist). Normally my pet was at 30%-40% when it came time to deal with the 2nd one. 2 blazes normally did the trick since it had been pounding on the DS for a while. <br>
<br>
Triple spiders will require some help. Never did pull a few to Norman and gate, but that might work.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
If you bind over by Icewell know that your mob will pop on top of you when Jibober bites it. I'd usually hang out a bit after the gate so that the mobs would probably have to deal with the Coldains on the way back home.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Many people on Innoruuk think nothing of paying 50p for the Coldain heads and often times they /auction for them in Thurgy. I've looted about 20 heads through 5 levels so don't expect to see them much (I did partner with another mage here several times so let's say 25 heads dropped total, about 1 per hour).<br>
